It seems that Roslyn doesn't consider null-coalescing assignments as assignments when inspeting which fields might end up uninitialized.
I see a couple of problems with this:
- Since it doesn't assign the variable only if it already is initialized there's nothing to warn about.
- It isn't consistent with other possible assignment sources e.g. passing the field as `ref` argument considered as initialization by Roslyn.

